 1.  Blinking with Transistor
\n Components needed: \n- Arduino UNO R3 *1 \n- Breadboard *1 \n- General Purpose Transistor NPN *1
\n- LED light bulb *1 \n- 1k ohm Resistor *2 \n- Jumper Wires *1 \n- 5V Power Source (Powerbank, laptop port of battery)
\n\n Software needed : \n Arduino IDE, Proteus (Schematic Diagram), Fritzing / Virtual Breadboard (Wiring Diagram).
\n\n Coding (Arduino IDE): \n

    const int transnpn = 2;

    \n\n void setup()
    \n {
    \n pinMode (transnpn, OUTPUT);
    \n}

    \n\n void loop()
    \n   {
    \n digitalWrite (transnpn, HIGH);
    \n delay(1500);
    \n digitalWrite (transnpn, LOW);
    \n delay(1500);
    \n }

